    <main>

        <article id="about">
            <h3>About MinecraftCon</h3>

            <p>
                <b>MinecraftCon</b> is an annual convention dedicated to celebrating
                the creativity, innovation, and community surrounding the game
                <cite>Minecraft</cite>.
            </p>

            <p>
                Since its first release, Minecraft has encouraged players to explore,
                build, and survive in a world made entirely of blocks. This event brings
                together fans who enjoy <mark>creative mode</mark>,
                <mark>survival gameplay</mark>, and <mark>technical design</mark>.
            </p>

            <blockquote>
                “Minecraft isn’t about the blocks — it’s about what you imagine you can build with them.”
            </blockquote>

            <p>
                Competitive events such as
                <abbr title="Player versus Player">PvP</abbr> tournaments and
                cooperative <abbr title="Player versus Environment">PvE</abbr> challenges
                allow attendees to test their skills.
            </p>
        </article>

        <article id="schedule">
            <h3>Convention Schedule</h3>

            <p>
                MinecraftCon takes place from
                <time datetime="2026-06-12">June 12, 2026</time> through
                <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>.
            </p>

            <pre>
Day 1: Opening Ceremony, Developer Panels, Redstone Workshops
Day 2: Build Competitions, PvP Tournaments, Creator Q&A
Day 3: Community Mega Build, Awards, Closing Remarks
            </pre>

            <p>
                Educational sessions demonstrate how commands like
                <code>/fill</code>, <code>/execute</code>, and <code>/tp</code>
                are used in advanced builds.
            </p>

            <q>Learning Minecraft commands is like learning a new language.</q>
        </article>

        <article id="tracks">
            <h3>Event Tracks</h3>

            <p>
                MinecraftCon offers several focused tracks designed for different
                play styles and interests.
            </p>

            <p>
                The <b>Builder Track</b> focuses on architecture, city planning,
                and large-scale world design using both <i>creative freedom</i>
                and <u>technical precision</u>.
            </p>

            <p>
                The <b>Technical Track</b> explores redstone engineering, automation,
                and optimization strategies used by expert players.
            </p>
        </article>

        <article id="community">
            <h3>Community & Culture</h3>

            <p>
                At its core, MinecraftCon is about community. Players from around
                the world gather to share ideas, collaborate on projects, and
                celebrate their love for the game.
            </p>

            <blockquote>
                “The best builds are the ones you make together.”
            </blockquote>

            <p>
                Community guidelines emphasize respect, creativity, and
                <mark>fair play</mark> in all convention events.
            </p>
        </article>

        <section id="location">
            <h3>Location & Venue</h3>

            <p>
                MinecraftCon 2026 will be hosted in Austin, Texas. The venue provides
                open spaces for exhibitions, competition arenas, and collaborative
                building areas.
            </p>

            <p>
                The city’s strong tech culture makes it an ideal location for a
                convention focused on creativity and innovation.
            </p>
        </section>

    </main>

    <aside>
        <h4>Quick Fact</h4>
        <p>
            Minecraft is one of the best-selling video games of all time, with a
            community that spans multiple generations of players.
        </p>
    </aside>

